---------- vim --------------
Insert: i
Save changes: :+w+q (use, ! to force; ‘:wq!’)
Exit without save: q!
Go to end of a word: shift+e
Go to start of the Line: shift+i
Go to last line of the file: shift+g
Go to first line of the file: g+g
Delete entire line: d+d
Undo a change: u
Indent a line: > + > or < + <
Indent 5 lines ahead: 5 + > + > 
Indent all the lines downwards: 999999 + > + >
Delete word from opposite end: shift + x

------------- bash --------------
for i in {1..3}; do kubectl run nginx$i --image=nginx; done (To have a loop in bash)
grep -i anything (Serach any character without being case sensative)
k get pods | cut -f 1 -d ' ' (Will give the first row delimiting using ' ', try this after running the loop command)
!k (Will run last command with k in it, '!k desc'; will also run last command with k in it, not the entire 'k desc')
!?k desc? (Will run the last instance of command having 'k desc' in it

